<!DOCTYPE suite SYSTEM "https://testng.org/testng-1.0.dtd" >
<suite name="Blue Rental Car" verbose="1" parallel="classes" thread-count="3">
    <test name="Parallel Test Classes" >
        <classes>

            <class name="techproed.tests.paralleltesting.Day22_ManagerLogin" />
            <class name="techproed.tests.paralleltesting.Day22_SearchItems" />
            <class name="techproed.tests.paralleltesting.Day22_TechproEducation" />

        </classes>
    </test>
</suite>

        <!--SUITE > TEST > PACKAGE > GROUPS > CLASSES > METHODS > INCLUDE OR EXCLUDE
        name  = any of the above
        verbose = The amount of info. The bigger number the more info
        To run on multiple browsers, add following information after verbose:
        parallel="true" thread-count="3"
        we can also change it into parallel="classes" to assign each class one browser  classes means run at class level

        If we turn parallel="false", it will run the tests in sequential order.

        SAVE YOUR XML FILES
        RUN YOUR XML FILE  -> RIGHT CLICK here or on the file
        This XML FILE serves as another way of grouping the tests/classes/packages etc.  that we want to run
        -->